=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Start from enantiopure trans-2-aminocyclohexane-1-carboxylic acid, protect the ring NH2 as Boc, then reduce CO2H → CH2OH (BH3·THF), convert CH2OH → CH2N3 (MsCl/NaN3), and hydrogenate to give N-Boc-2-amino-1-(aminomethyl)cyclohexane | Step 2: Prepare the heteroaryl electrophile 2,4,6-trichloro-5-fluoropyrimidine and the chlorinated azaindole partner as the corresponding boronic ester/acid from c2c[nH]c3ncc(Cl)cc23 | Step 3: Suzuki couple the azaindole boronic ester onto the pyrimidine core (at the most activated C4) to give 4-(azaindolyl)-2,6-dichloro-5-fluoropyrimidine | Step 4: SNAr with the free aminomethyl group of the protected cyclohexane diamine at one remaining chloro to form the N-Boc side-chain adduct | Step 5: Ammonolysis of the last chloro to install the exocyclic NH2, then remove Boc with HCl/dioxane to furnish N[C@@H]1CCCC[C@H]1CNc1nc(-c2c[nH]c3ncc(Cl)cc23)ncc1F

